race.description: Thoroughbred Club Of Australia Mdn Plate
race.comment: TOWER BRIDGE (7) is an expensive colt ($1.3 million) by champion sire I Am Invincible who debuts here for the Mark Walker yard. He's won a trial impressively leading in and draws well. Expecting he measures right up. ROYAL HONOUR (6) was good on debut at Cranbourne over this trip, going down by a neck when showing early speed. Better for that effort and maps well here, he can go one better. ESPANA (8) has had a few chances but is going well, through a good maiden last time at Ballarat when third. She should be hard to hold out. GRAM (2) was just fair fresh at Mornington when in the market but was off a very long spell (16 months) there and should strip much fitter.
